    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters May 4th with a clear objective: maximize stolen base upside while exploiting defensive liabilities. **Mickey Moniak** (73.15) stands as our premier play today, leveraging a massive +14% park factor against Brazob\u00e1n. While the opposing battery presents a challenge for base stealers with a 1.87s exchange time, **Mickey Moniak**\u2019s lead-off positioning and platoon advantage make him the pivot point of the lineup. Similarly, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.58) and **Josh Naylor** (70.81) provide elite stability in the heart of the order, benefiting from favorable SP skill metrics and consistent run-production potential. **Seiya Suzuki** (67.84) also grades out as a top-tier start, as he is perfectly positioned to punish a weak matchup against Petty (6.57 xERA), where his +19% SP skill boost carries him into elite territory.\n\nOur most difficult decision involved the infield, where **Cole Young** (48.11) narrowly missed the final utility spot. While **Cole Young** possesses the contact profile we covet, the projection model opted for the higher ceiling of **Jose Caballero** (47.55) and **Kyle Karros** (45.92) due to their specific role-playing utility and despite the defensive hurdles presented by the opposing catcher. The choice to bench **Austin Riley** (42.82) was purely matchup-driven; facing Gilbert (3.04 xERA) significantly deflated his efficiency, making him a liability in our Roto format today compared to the more favorable spots assigned to **Travis Bazzana** (53.25) and **Trevor Story** (59.52). \n\nRisks for today are concentrated in the late-order slots. **Jose Caballero** remains a high-variance play; while we value his speed, the -13% platoon adjustment and a bottom-tier batting order position create a precarious floor. Furthermore, the battery of Brazob\u00e1n is specifically optimized to suppress our stolen base targets, meaning **Mickey Moniak** and **Kyle Karros** will need to be extremely opportunistic on the basepaths to maintain their value. With **Corbin Carroll** sidelined due to a team off-day, we are relying on our depth to carry the load; ensure all lineup confirmations are monitored for last-minute defensive replacements.",
